strings:
<voice_0x01001683><se_low>Yangus: We done it, guv!
We only went and bleedin' done it!
<voice_0x01001684><se_high>Jessica: At last! I can finally go back and tell Bangerz and Mash it's all over.

<voice_0x01001685><se_high>Jessica: And I have something to tell Alistair, too...
That he was right all along. I only made it this far because I followed my heart.
<voice_0x01001687><se_def>Angelo: ...Who'd have thought we'd ever manage it!? Hm, should be an interesting anecdote for the ladies!

<voice_0x0100168A><se_low>Yangus: I bet Grandad an' the 'orse-princess'll be 'avin'
a whale of a time by now! 
They must be back to normal at last!
<voice_0x0100168B><se_low>Yangus: I'm 'alf surprised the old codger ain't turned up to surprise us as usual...
<voice_0x0100168C><se_low>Yangus: But even 'e couldn't spring up in a place like this, eh? Ha ha ha ha hah!

<voice_0x0100168D><center>I transported your friends
<center>back to their homeland.
<voice_0x0100168F><center>I will never forget your strength and courage.

<voice_0x01001690><center>You remind me of the seven sages.
<center>You humans never fail to surprise me.

<voice_0x01001691><center>It is time to land.
<center>Your friends are eager to see you again.

<voice_0x01001692><center>Here we are.
<center>Now you can be with your friends again.

<voice_0x01001693><se_low>King Trode: Ah, there you are!
Welcome back!

<voice_0x01001694><se_low>King Trode: I saw you all in action!
My wonderful men!
You were magnificent!
<voice_0x01001695><se_low>Yangus: I ain't one of your men, Grandad!
<voice_0x01001698><se_high>Jessica: Neither am I!
<voice_0x01001699><se_def>Angelo: And I'm a free agent!

<voice_0x0100169C><se_low>King Trode: ...Hm!? Ha ha ha ha hah! Of course, of course!
And I suppose you weren't magnificent, either!

<voice_0x0100169D><se_low>King Trode: Wise bird...er, god...!
I...er... Are you leaving us already?

<voice_0x0100169E><center>This world is in no danger now.
<center>My path leads to other worlds.

<voice_0x0100169F><se_low>King Trode: ...I see. Well anyway, we are in your de<endash>
Wait a minute! Aren't you forgetting something!?

<voice_0x010016A0><se_low>King Trode: What about the Princess and I, hm?
Just how long are we going to have to
suffer this outrageous curse!?
<voice_0x010016A1><center>Well...

<voice_0x010016A2><center>...The power of Rhapthorne's curse is weakening.
<center>It will not be long now.

<voice_0x010016A3><se_low>King Trode: Really!? Splendid!
I feel much better for hearing that!
<voice_0x010016A4><se_low>King Trode: Well, I don't know where your next destination is, but take care!
<voice_0x010016A5><se_low>King Trode: ...I-Is it proper to tell a god to take care?

<voice_0x010016A6><center>I am not a god. Nor is my real name Empyrea.
<center>These are but the names you humans
<center>have given to me.

<voice_0x010016A7><center>I was known by a different name
<center>in the land of my birth...
<voice_0x010016A8><center>There I was called...Ramia.

<voice_0x010016A9><center>But now I must leave.
<center>Goodbye, brave humans.
<center>It has been an honour to have known you.
<voice_0x010016AA><se_low>King Trode: ...Goodbye...
<voice_0x010016AB><se_low>Yangus: G-Grandad! You're sparklin'!

<voice_0x010016AC><se_low>King Trode: Hm! It's taken you this long to notice!?
A personality as rich as mine always sparkles!

<voice_0x010016AD><se_low>Yangus: Nah, I mean literally!
Take a look at yerself!
<voice_0x010016AE><se_low>King Trode: ...Hm?
<voice_0x010016AF><se_low>King Trode: Oooh!
<voice_0x010016B0><se_low>King Trode: I-I-I'm back to normal!

<voice_0x010016B1><se_low>King Trode: Hurrah! I'm back!
Finally rid of that hideously ugly guise!

<voice_0x010016B2><se_low>Yangus: But...
Ya don't look no different!
You look exactly the same as before! Ha ha ha!
<voice_0x010016B3><se_low>King Trode: WHAT did you say!? Are you BLIND!?
<voice_0x010016B4><se_low>King Trode: Dazzled by my striking appearance, no doubt!
<voice_0x010016B5><se_low>King Trode: Wait! This is no time for an argument!

<voice_0x010016B6><se_low>King Trode: Where's the Princess?
Where is my beautiful Medea?
<voice_0x010016B7><se_high>Princess Medea: Hello, everyone...

<voice_0x010016B8><se_low>King Trode: Medea! You're back!
Oh, my beloved Medea!

<voice_0x010016B9><se_low>King Trode: At last! At last the curse is lifted!
Everything is back as it should be!
<voice_0x010016BA><se_high>Princess Medea: Father...
<voice_0x010016BB><se_high>Jessica: Hey! Look!

<voice_0x010016BC><se_low>King Trode: Oooh! My castle!
My castle is back to its old self too!

<voice_0x010016BD><se_low>King Trode: Trodain is restored! The glory returns!
Everyone! This calls for a banquet!
Prepare a feast!

<voice_0x01001688><se_high>Red: Blimey... That was flippin' mental, weren't it?
But now it's all over, I feel a bit...bored.
<voice_0x01001689><se_low>Morrie: Ah ha ha, even the big fat Lord of the Darkness is no match for our GUSTO!
<voice_0x0100168E><center>Brave heroes...
<voice_0x01001696><se_high>Jessica: Um, excuse me, but in case you hadn't noticed, I'm not a man, and I'm certainly not yours!

<voice_0x01001697><se_def>Angelo: Your men? Sorry, Your Majesty, but I don't
recall swearing allegiance to Trodain.
I'm really not one for commitment.
<voice_0x0100169A><se_high>Red: No one tells me wot to do, mate.

<voice_0x0100169B><se_low>Morrie: Si, I am magnifico!
But I am not yours, Don Toad.
